    "summary": "Paul has more than 18 years\u2019 experience as controller in the field of drawing up reports, dashboards, KPI\u2019s, forecasts, financial statements (Dutch GAAP, IFRS and US GAAP), investment analysis, due diligences, M&A\u2019s, valuations, cash flow statements, consolidations and tax planning\u2019s in large and medium-sized enterprises (TNT Express, Philips, DSM, ING, CompuGroup, RWE, Ministry of Transport, Public Works and Water Management and VodafoneZiggo). Managerial capacities both with managing large departments as well as coaching employees and delegating tasks and responsibilities and finding good cooperation with other departments within the organization. I have managed various Financial Departments (7 up to 85 Employees), including FSSC's of TNT Express and RWE. I have gained a lot of experience with SAP (all cycles) and Hyperion. I have a strong analytical ability to analyze figures quickly. I have a hands-on approach and I am always willing to support where needed.     \n\nPaul has more than 10 years\u2019 experience as business process specialist and project manager in the field of designing, implementing, improving and testing internal control frameworks for large, multinational organisations such as Philips, Ricoh, ASML, Rockwool, Tyco, Merck, Dutch Railways, Nexperia and advisor to the Board of Management of Imtech. In addition, he has 6 years of experience as an internal auditor at DSM and Akzo-Nobel and as audit manager at PwC and IT audit manager at Deloitte.\n\nPaul has a hands-on approach with managing projects and financial transformations. Paul has gained extensive experience with SAP ECC (all end-to-end processes). In addition, Paul is an expert in Master Data management, System roles and SoD\u2019s within SAP ECC.  \n\nPaul is also freelance lecturer in external reporting, internal control and corporate finance at various institutions.\n",
